posts.name: Terry Lin
posts.cooked:
During loading the weights, error reported as following:

ORTE has lost communication with a remote daemon.

HNP daemon : [[41677,0],0] on node spark-c3c9

Remote daemon: [[41677,0],1] on node 169.254.22.181

posts.name: Terry Lin
posts.cooked: after turning the debug option, it shows error code 137, which means OOM. I tried to lower the gpu memory fraction, but not work either.

posts.name: Aniculescu
posts.cooked: Hi, can you give more details on how you are deploying this model? Reproduction steps and logs would be very helpful

posts.name: Terry Lin
posts.cooked:
I am following the instructions from this link dgx-spark-playbooks/nvidia/trt-llm/README.md at main · NVIDIA/dgx-spark-playbooks · GitHub
If I use the model gpt-oss-120b instead of Qwen3-235B-A22B-FP4 , this case can be run successfully.
all of the output is the same as the link showed, except the last step for launching the mpirun, which timeout loading weights.
I checked on the remote node, and I found out the memory is drained.

posts.name: Aniculescu
posts.cooked:

posts.name: Terry Lin
posts.cooked:
thanks for the information.
finally, I figure out what went wrong. although the guide in the playbook does not mention the required version of tensorrt-llm, but in the logs, it shows 1.0.0rc3,
But I tried the latest version which is 1.2.0rc1, that was not working, even though the final release of 1.0.0 does not work either.
And finally, I tried with the 1.0.0rc3 version, and it work! So this looks like a bug of the newer version of tensorrt-llm.
